tourBios.curYrHigh: Joined PGA TOUR Latinoamérica with a T8 finish at the Mazatlán, Mexico Q-School in January.
tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Made five cuts in 10 starts on PGA TOUR Canada, with his best finish a T19 at Cape Breton Classic in September. 

2013: Played PGA TOUR Canada, making five cuts in nine starts. Had two top 10s—including a runner-up finish at The Great Waterway Classic. Shot a final-round 62 to finish one shot behind Hugo Leon resulting in a solo-second finish, his best on PGA TOUR Canada...Second top 10 was at the Tour Championship Canada (T10). Finished 21st on the Order of Merit. 

2012: Shot a final-round 65 to finish T6 at the Jamieson WFCU Windsor Roseland Charity Classic...Missed the cut in his one Web.com Tour start, the WNB Classic in Midland, Texas.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Qualified for the NCAA National Championship every year while at Chino State… Won the 2007 California State Fair Championship… Was first-team all-league in high school golf while he attended Las Lomas High School in Walnut Creek, California.
tourBios.personal: Brother Bo is an accomplished fisherman... Favorite course played is Spyglass Hill... Favorite pro teams are the San Francisco Giants, San Francisco 49ers and the Golden State Warriors... Favorite TV show is "Law and Order" and favorite movie is "Dumb and Dumber."... Favorite athlete is Buster Posey... Favorite vacation spot is Telluride, Colo... Would like to trade places with the President of the United States for one day... Dream foursome would be his grandpa, Arnold Palmer and George W. Bush... Not many people know he's a great dancer... Would like to be featured in Field and Stream for "catching the world's record bass."... First-tee intro song would be anything by his favorite performer, Luke Bryan... Twitter name is @brandonharkins1… Instagram name is @brandonharks
